/www.cjr.org/first_person/beyond-the-truth-o-meter.php","uid":"beyond-the-truth-o-meter-by-cjr"}}},{"node":{"id":"a9e34ffc-7a57-5413-8fb6-f95c2c3e32d3","html":"<p>Dan Schultz, Ted Han, and Carolyn Rupar are part of the Bad Idea Factory’s crew for reprising Schultz’s MIT Media Lab 2011 graduate thesis project: Truth Goggles...</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"April 2018","title":"Truth Goggles are back! And ready for the next era of fact-checking","cover":null,"link":null,"highlight":false,"publication":"NiemanLab","source":"http://www.niemanlab.org/2018/04/truth-goggles-are-back-and-ready-for-the-next-era-of-fact-checking/","uid":"truth-goggles-are-back"}}},{"node":{"id":"dc2e8acc-fe4b-571c-8c4f-5e48da3481e8","html":"<p>Let’s say a friend posts a YouTube video link to a politician’s statement on Facebook, but you have a feeling it’s taken out of context. The clip is tightly edited, and you’re curious to see the rest of the statement. Was the politician answering a question? Was the statement part of a larger discussion?</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"March 2018","title":"Glorious ContextuBot making progress","cover":null,"link":null,"highlight":false,"publication":"Internet Archive Blogs","source":"https://blog.archive.org/2018/03/08/tv-news-record-glorious-contextubot-making-progress/","uid":"glorious-contextubot-making-progress"}}},{"node":{"id":"2da1577e-666b-5bc0-893b-92b1eb3226f7","html":"<p>Beyond citizen engagement and fact-checking to educate and build trust, these projects incorporate technology, like gaming and machine learning. The Glorious ContextuBot, for example, provides the original source of sound bites and lets you know when they aired on the news. Another project uses algorithms to score web-based journalism for quality in real-time.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"September 2017","title":"New Solutions Emerge to Fight Fake News","cover":null,"link":null,"highlight":false,"publication":"Hand Foundation","source":"http://thehandfoundation.org/newsletter-article.php?New-Solutions-Emerge-to-Fight-Fake-News-157","uid":"new-solutions-emerge-to-fight-fake-news"}}},{"node":{"id":"675da742-43e9-54fc-b480-976f53a8f50d","html":"<p>The Knight Prototype Fund will give $1 million to 20 projects designed to fight fake news, stop the spread of misinformation and increase trust in journalism....</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"July 2017","title":"Knight Foundation To Give $1 Million To 20 Projects To Fight Fake News","cover":null,"link":null,"highlight":false,"publication":"Forbes","source":"https://www.forbes.com/sites/paulfletcher/2017/06/26/knight-foundation-to-give-1-million-to-20-projects-to-fight-fake-news/","uid":"knight-to-give-1-million"}}}]}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"uid":"media"}}